@kmarlen1988, can you confirm whether your intent to limited to prediction or to retrain a complete model? It seems like you attempted to launch training on cpu, which is likely not a good idea as it would takes ages to train large model such as Inception or Resnet on cpu. 

If you want to use a pre-trained model to perform prediction, you can look at the steps here: http://dmlc.ml/rstats/2015/12/08/image-classification-shiny-app-mxnet-r.html

As you seemed to have only 2 classes, if what you want is to fine tune a pre-existing model, you can look here: https://statist-bhfz.github.io/cats_dogs_finetune Again, training on GPU is highly desirable for this task.

