Thanks, it turned out that there is another setting on smt solvers that prevent candidate models from being produced. The option is fail_if_inconclusive. It takes precedence, or rather, it took precedence according to previous behavior. This confused me when trying out the repro, so I have it now that candidate_models take precedence. While fail_if_inconclusive is by default "true" it gets ignored if candidate_models is "true" (it is by default false).
You can either pick up the latest check-in and build yourself, wait for a build, or you can add the following to your code:

     Params params = context.mkParams();
     params.add("candidate_models", true);
     params.add("fail_if_inconclusive", false);
     solver.setParameters(params);

