@minrk, got it. I'll put some thought into a backward compatible solution here.

I just want to check in and see whether we are all still in favor of cross validating defaults though.

IMO it makes sense to enforce uniform behavior when assigning all new values. If we fail to cross validate defaults, there is a discrepancy between the way we handle default values, and every other value a user might set.
